  "body": "### Description\n\nI've noticed @sschellh commenting in #31079 that having unique (state) cookie names is not good if whitelisting cookies is required:\r\n```\r\nUnique cookie names have in my point of view the disadvantage that in certain situations you want to explicitly whitelist the cookie names. For instance in a AWS CloudFront [Origin Request Policy](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSCloudFormation/latest/UserGuide/aws-properties-cloudfront-originrequestpolicy-cookiesconfig.html).\r\n```\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nUnique state cookie name is required for multi-tab authentication to work but users can disable it - however, right now, even if they disable it, the state cookie name will remain unique - so we just have to make sure no UUID is added to state cookie name if no multi-tab authentication is required - there is no need to have a unique state cookie name in such case",
